<L>__{exterior runway cecil field, fla. day}
<A>__{ecker jumps down from the cockpit ladder and turns an eye to his battered, pock marked plane. wilhemy and the ground crew chief come running up, the chief letting out a whistle.}
<C>__{ground crew chief}
<D>__{lookit what daddy done brung home.}
<C>__{wilhemy}
<D>__{you shoulda seen it, chief, they }
<C>__{ecker}
<D>__{ damn sparrows. must've been migrating. guess i hit a couple hundred.}
<P>__{(to wilhemy, stern)}
<D>__{how many did you hit, bruce?}
<A>__{wilhemy stands there, looking at ecker, not sure what to make of him. the crew chief just starts laughing as more impressed ground crew come up.}
<C>__{wilhemy}
<D>__{a few. i guess.}
<C>__{ground crew chief}
<D>__{was them 20 or 40 million sparrows?}
<A>__{ecker, sweat plastered and foul, steps into the chief's face.}
<C>__{ecker}
<D>__{those are bird strikes. sparrows to be precise. got a problem with that?}
<A>__{the chief stands there, glances at the plane one more time, and shakes his head, 'no.' ecker takes the chief's maintenance clipboard from him, writes in big bold marker: bird strikes. he thrusts it back into the chief's hands and walks off; the astonished wilhemy remains behind.}
